SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 51
BY SENATOR JACKSON-ANDREWS AND REPRESENTATIVES FISHER AND
MOORE
COMMENDATIONS. Commends and congratulates the Wossman High School girls'
basketball team for winning their fifth-straight state championship.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend and congratulate the Wossman High School Lady Wildcats basketball team
3 on capturing their fifth-straight state championship.
4 WHEREAS, the Louisiana High School Athletic Association (LHSAA) annually
5 conducts the state basketball championships to showcase the highest level of high school
6 athletic competition across Louisiana; and
7 WHEREAS, the Wossman High School Lady Wildcats have established themselves
8 as one of the premier high school girls' basketball programs in the state through exceptional
9 performance, teamwork, and dedication; and
10 WHEREAS, under the leadership of Head Coach Otis Robinson, the Lady Wildcats
11 have achieved remarkable success during his first five seasons, compiling an impressive
12 139-25 overall record and advancing to the state championship game each year; and
13 WHEREAS, on March 7, 2026, at the University Center at Southeastern Louisiana
14 University, Wossman defeated LaGrange High School by a score of 50-39 in the Division
15 II Non-Select championship game; and
16 WHEREAS, the victory secured the Lady Wildcats' fifth consecutive state
17 championship, an extraordinary accomplishment that reflects the program's sustained
18 excellence, discipline, and commitment to success; and
