1 WHEREAS, Wossman set the tone early in the championship contest by opening the
2 game with a dominant performance that produced a 16-1 lead at the conclusion of the first
3 quarter; and
4 WHEREAS, sophomore Heaven Weeks delivered a remarkable performance and was
5 named the game's Most Outstanding Player after recording twenty-six points, sixteen
6 rebounds, four steals, one assist, and one block; and
7 WHEREAS, junior MaKaiya Johnson contributed significantly to the win with
8 eleven points, ten rebounds, four steals, and an assist, while sophomore London Landers
9 added seven points, nine rebounds, and two assists to help secure the victory; and
10 WHEREAS, the 2025-2026 Wossman Lady Wildcats basketball team is led by Head
11 Coach Otis Robinson Jr., Assistant Coaches Gerline Guillaume, Angel Coleman, and
12 Martina Johnson; and
13 WHEREAS, displaying unwavering grit and discipline are players Morgan Wilhite,
14 Heaven Weeks, London Landers, MaKaiya Johnson, Krysten Lewis, Errieunna Artis, Taylar
15 Wright, Ashanti Smith, Lyrics Robinson, Anesti Johnson, Kaitlynn Timber, Isabella Jones,
16 Jade Robinson, and Antonia Collins, supported by team managers, Wil'lashai Cherry and
17 Jamaiyah Scoby; and
18 WHEREAS, the Lady Wildcats' continued success reflects not only outstanding
19 athletic ability but also a strong commitment to academic excellence, teamwork, and positive
20 character both on and off the court; and
21 WHEREAS, the Wossman High School players, coaches, faculty, and supporters
22 have brought great pride and distinction to the school, the city of Monroe, and the state of
23 Louisiana through their outstanding achievements.
24 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
25 commend and congratulate the Wossman Lady Wildcats upon winning the LHSAA 2026
26 Division II Non-Select state championship and achieving the extraordinary milestone of five
27 consecutive state titles.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to Otis
29 Robinson, head coach of the Wossman High School Lady Wildcats basketball team, and
30 Dena Sampson, principal of Wossman High School.
